You are given an array of integers. Your task is to find the maximum product of any two elements in the array.

Input Format

The first line contains an integer n, representing the size of the array.

The second line contains n space-separated integers, representing the array elements.

Constraints

NA

Output Format

Print a single integer, the maximum product of any two elements in the array.

Sample Input 0

5
1 2 3 4 5
Sample Output 0

20
Explanation 0

The maximum product is 4 * 5 = 20.

Sample Input 1

4
-10 -3 5 -6
Sample Output 1

60
Explanation 1

The maximum product is -10 * -6 = 60 (product of two negative numbers is positive).



import java.util.*;
public class Solution {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
        int n=sc.nextInt();
        int[] a=new int[n];
        for (int i=0;i<n;i++) {
            a[i]=sc.nextInt();
        }
        int m= Integer.MIN_VALUE;
        for (int i=0;i<n;i++) {
            for (int j=i+1;j<n;j++) {
                m=Math.max(m,a[i]*a[j]);
            }
        }
        System.out.print(m);
    }
}


